parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HPFP can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, the failure can cause metal shavings to contaminate the fuel system, leading to further damage and costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the glow plug light and check engine light come on
the vehicle goes into limp mode
and the fuel system becomes contaminated with metal shavings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel contamination and misfueling can cause the HPFP to fail, leading to engine stalling and loss of power, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the fuel system becomes contaminated with gasoline or other substances
and the vehicle may experience difficulty starting or running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the fuel system becomes contaminated with metal shavings or other substances
and the vehicle may experience difficulty starting or running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DSG transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle revs freely as if in neutral
the vehicle slows down or stalls
and the transmission may eventually re-engage on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle dies or stalls
and the fuel pump may explode
causing metal shavings to enter the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle control system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's control system fails
turning off power steering
ABS brakes
and shifting the transmission to neutral
and preventing windows from opening.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The freezing of the intercooler can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle struggles to start
stalls
and water builds up in the intercooler piping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HPFP can cause the engine to stall or lose power, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light or glow plug light flashes
the vehicle goes into "limp" mode
the fuel pump fails
and metal shavings are found in the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including loss of lights, engine stalling, and even fires, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of lights
including headlights
brake lights
and turn signals
engine stalling
burning smell
electrical shorts
and fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and even fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents or fires.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
fuel leaks
metallic debris in the high-pressure pump bore
and fuel system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and performance issues can cause loss of power, stalling, and even accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
dashboard warning lights
and near-miss accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as the airbag may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in a crash
the airbag deployed late or delayed
the airbag did not deploy at all
the vehicle was recalled for a Takata airbag issue
but parts were not available for repair
the manufacturer refused to provide a safe alternative transportation or repair the vehicle in a reasonable amount of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to a lack of warning to other drivers or pedestrians, potentially causing accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The horn failed to work
the horn needed to be replaced
the horn was related to the airbag being electrically connected.
